Match database search result order to  LibGuides AZ database search

comments.body:
Springshare's response: 

Both the A-Z Databases search and the LibGuides Search page results are determined by term relevancy with each field given equal weight. 

- For A-Z database searches, these are the fields that are present when adding or editing a database:
description, keywords, librarian note, more info, name, slug/friendly URL, subjects, URL, and vendor name

- The more times the search term(s) appear in these fields, the higher it will be ranked in the search results.

So it may be that "Oxford Scholarship Online: Music" has more mentions of Oxford and/or Music in its description, keywords, etc. than "Oxford Music" does and thus is shown higher on the results list.

orangelight.title: Facets from regular search are not transferred to drop-down on Advanced search form
When editing search, the search term is populated in both the basic and advanced search fields
i3734: Edit basic search with new advanced search form

comments.body:
[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/62880483/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/62880483)

coverage: 95.437% (+0.03%) from 95.409% when pulling **8524e80ac59b4e3894d3432c8c74e88946a89dbf on i3734-search-terms** into **ec7b6115b0b10cf09a7006ec7feab9b8706ca044 on main**.

I definitely think this is an improvement, and I'm not sure whether the following refinements should be a future ticket or part of this ticket:
- The search term is still in the basic search box, which could lead to confusion
![Search term is in both the basic keyword search box and the advanced keyword search box](https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/assets/45948126/422a48e9-3302-4b96-ae61-ebf1641da5e0)

- The field being searched isn't transferred to the advanced search form, e.g.
  - Start with basic search
  - Select "Author (keyword)" from basic search dropdown
  - Type "Kilmer, Joyce" in search box
  - Click "Search"
  - Click "Edit search"
  - I would expect the term to be transferred to the "Author/Creator" advanced search, but it's transferred into the keyword search
![The author search "Kilmer, Joyce" transferred into the advanced keyword search, not the also visible "Author/Creator" search](https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/assets/45948126/d31d2fb6-f4d2-4948-9e68-092859df3ff7)
Thanks, @maxkadel !  I opened the first as a new ticket #3760, and pushed a new commit to address the second issue you found.

princeton_ansible.title: Add headers to help troubleshooting error pages
[ruby_s] Move bundler out of install into main
Mount the peoplesoft directory every playbook run.
Use a template for our simplest nginx configs

comments.body:
A quick look at a few config files uncovers a few differences among sites. Known needed changes:
- [x] add a var for the HTTP [load-balancing technique](https://www.nginx.com/blog/choosing-nginx-plus-load-balancing-techniques/) (see annotations-prod)
- [x] add a section for enabling/disabling `app_protect` (see abid-staging)
- [x] allow more than one included `restrict` file (see bibdata-qa)
- [x] regularize an `ansible-managed` comment

With these changes done, we can try using the template for these sites:
- [x] abid
- [x] annotations
- [x] ansible-tower
- [x] approvals
- [x] bibdata
- [x] byzantine-tsp
- [ ] cicognara
- [ ] eal-apps
. . . and probably more.

Once the changes are ready, we can put the vars in place and create the templated files in `/tmp/`, then diff the files against the actual nginxplus config files to identify any changes/drift.
